    "language": "english",
    "persons": [],
    "text": "April 20 (Reuters) - Irish software firm Ion Investment Group Ltd said on Friday it had approached Fidessa Group with a proposal to buy the British software firm for 38.703 pounds per share, potentially countering a 1.4 billion pound ($1.96 billion) deal by Switzerland’s Temenos.\nIon said it approached Fidessa’s board and certain shareholders with the proposal, under which Fidessa shareholders would also get a special and final dividend totalling 79.7 pence per share. ($1 = 0.7115 pounds) (Reporting by Rahul B in Bengaluru; Editing by Gopakumar Warrier)\n ",
